      <span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between crawling and indexing?</span>
      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="what-is-the-difference-between-crawling-and-indexi"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Crawling is discovery. Google finds your page by following a link or reading your sitemap. Indexing is storage. Google analyzes the page content and adds it to its database. A page can be crawled but not indexed if Google decides the content is not valuable enough.</p></div></div>
  </div>
